                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12576287" author="stack" created="Fri, 7 Mar 2008 17:32:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I like the idea of using the configured filesystem and defaulting local filesystem (if tests on windows pass on local filesystem).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Jim, did you ever get chance at figuring why recursive delete is not working when on local filesystem on windows though seems to work when you do ./bin/hadoop -rmr /SOME_DIR_WITH_SUBDIRS on your windows machine?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12576352" author="jimk" created="Fri, 7 Mar 2008 19:57:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FsShell has a special version of delete that works recursively. FileSystem.delete is not recursive. It works on unix because you can remove a directory if it is not empty. No so on Windows.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, when we delete directories, we might want to use FileUtil.fullyDelete instead of FileSystem.delete and that should solve the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12576356" author="stack" created="Fri, 7 Mar 2008 20:05:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Great.  We can call this at end of test?  Shall we start in on a refactor of tests that cuts out spin up of minidfs and that instead just reads the filesystem to use from $HBASE_HOME/src/test/hbase-site.xml?  (On hudson can fill this file w/ the hdfs to use)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12579566" author="bryanduxbury" created="Mon, 17 Mar 2008 19:37:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sub-issue was more important that parent issue. Correcting.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12766386" author="stack" created="Fri, 16 Oct 2009 03:05:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Running a dfscluster for length of test is what hbase-410 is about.  Marking this closed as duplicate.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15017892" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 13:01:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was closed as part of a bulk closing operation on 2015-11-20. All issues that have been resolved and where all fixVersions have been released have been closed (following discussions on the mailing list).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
